<FIRST>r a BC-HeadlinerAwards     03-11 0448</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Headliner Awards,0468</SECOND>
<HEAD>National Headliner Award Winners Announced</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTIC CITY, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Arizona Republic, the Roanoke
Times and World News, and Newsweek magazine were among top winners
in the 1989 National Headliners Awards announced this week in this
seaside resort.
   The Arizona Republic received the award for outstanding
investigative reporting for a series of stories examining the use
and misuse of drugs on elderly people. The stories were written by
Mike Masterson and Chuck Cook.
   Mary Bishop of the Roanoke Times and World News won the
outstanding public service award for ``Poison In Our Homes,'' a
series on exterminators and the effects of little regulation of the
industry.
   Newsweek magazine's coverage of the presidential election
received the award for outstanding coverage of a major news event
for magazines and syndicates. Newsweek writer Bill Carol also was
cited for his consistently outstanding feature writing for a
magazine or syndicate.
   Other first-place winners include:
   _ OUTSTANDING NEWS REPORTING BY A NEWSPAPER, CIRCULATION TO
50,000: David Gomez and Patricia Guthrie, The Albuquerque Tribune,
``Gallup,'' the alcohol problems in Gallup, N.M.
   _ OUTSTANDING NEWS REPORTING BY A NEWSPAPER, CIRCULATION 50,000
TO 150,000: Anchorage Daily News staff, ``Alaska Natives, A People
in Peril.''
   _ OUTSTANDING NEWS REPORTING BY A NEWSPAPER, CIRCULATION OVER
150,000: Louisville Courier-Journal staff, for coverage of the
Carrollton, Ky., bus crash.
   _ CONSISTENTLY OUTSTANDING LOCAL INTEREST COLUMN: Roger Simon,
The Baltimore Sun.
   _ CONSISTENTLY OUTSTANDING COLUMN ON ONE SUBJECT: Jim Dwyer,
Newsday, In The Subways.
   _ CONSISTENTLY OUTSTANDING EDITORIAL CARTOONS: Walt Handelsman,
The Scranton Times.
   _ OUTSTANDING SPOT NEWS PHOTOGRAPHY: Ron Olshwanger, St. Louis
Post-Dispatch, for photo of a baby rescued from fire.
   _ OUTSTANDING FEATURE PHOTOGRAPHY: Ben DeSoto, Houston Chronicle,
for photo of cowboy choreography.
   _ OUTSTANDING SPORTS PHOTOGRAPHY: Brian Smith, Miami Herald, for
photo of diver Greg Louganis hitting the board.
   _ CONSISTENTLY OUTSTANDING SPORTS WRITING: Terry Egan, The Times
Herald-Record, Middletown, N.Y.
   _ CONSISTENTLY OUTSTANDING FEATURE WRITING: Daniel Golden, The
Boston Globe.
   _ CONSISTENTLY OUTSTANDING COLUMN BY A MAGAZINE OR SYNDICATE:
Judith Stone, Discover magazine.
   _ OUTSTANDING SPOT NEWS PHOTO BY A MAGAZINE OR SYNDICATE: Ramazan
Ozturk, Time magazine, for photo of mustard gas attack victims.
   _ OUTSTANDING FEATURE PHOTO BY A MAGAZINE OR SYNDICATE: Jeff
Widener, Associated Press, for photo of a man cleaning skulls titled
``The Killing Field.''
   _ OUTSTANDING SPORTS PHOTO BY A MAGAZINE OR SYNDICATE: Dieter
Endlicher, Associated Press, for photo of a track star titled ``The
Fastest Woman.''
   Winners in the broadcast categories will be announced later this
month. The awards weekend will be June 2 and 3 in Atlantic City.
   The National Headliners Awards, now in its 55th year, are
sponsored by the Press Club of Atlantic City.
</TEXT>
