<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--SriLankaFire     03-11 0115</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Sri Lanka Fire,0115</SECOND>
<HEAD>Oil Refinery Fire Spurs Panic</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLOMBO, Sri Lanka (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An oil-refinery tank caught fire during
a thunderstorm and hundreds of residents fled in panic as smoke and
fumes enveloped the area, police reported.
   They said there were no casualties from Friday's blaze at the
state-owned refinery in Sapugaskande, 10 miles north of Colombo, and
the fire apparently was caused by lightning.
   ``People began running from their homes near the refinery fearing
the fire would spread to the other 24 tanks'' in the refinery, a
police official said.
   The tanks set afire contained naphtha and rain helped firemen
bring the blaze under control within two hours, according to the
police.
</TEXT>
