<HEAD>Ambassador to Japan Named</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush has nominated undersecretary of
state Michael Armacost to be ambassador to Japan, succeeding Mike
Mansfield.
   Armacost's selection had been known for weeks but was not
formally announced by the White House until Friday. Since 1984,
Armacost has been the State Department's undersecretary for
political affairs, following a two-year stint as ambassador to the
Philippines.
   From 1980 until 1981, Armacost served as principal deputy
assistant secretary of state for East Asian and Pacific Affairs.
