<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Socialist International, an
organization of left-wing political and government leaders,
denounced the Czechoslovak government's crackdown on dissidents.
   In the past month, at least 12 activists have been convicted in
Czechoslovak courts on a variety of charges.
   During Friday's closing session of a two-day conference, former
West German Chancellor Willy Brandt, president of the Socialist
International, praised moves toward reform in some East bloc
countries.
   But he criticized Czechoslovakia for its treatment of dissidents.
