Havel, the country's leading human rights campaigner.
   Havel, whose works are banned in his country, was convicted last
month of incitement and obstructing police after participating in
demonstrations. He was sentenced to nine months in prison.
   Brandt also said the Socialist International planned to hold a
``fact-finding'' meeting on the Middle East in Brussels, Belgium in
May.
   ``We hope members of the U.N. Security Council will be present as
well as representatives from Israel, and Palestinians,'' he said.
   He did not say whether the Palestine Liberation Organization
would be invited. Israel considers the group a terrorist
organization and refuses to participate in peace talks with it.
