<SECOND>AM-Autistic Abandon,0180</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bus Driver Who Left Autistic Boy On Bus Overnight Fired</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A school bus driver who unknowingly left a
mentally impaired 9-year-old boy overnight on her bus in freezing
weather has been fired, school officials said.
   Belinda Rounds, 27, was fired Friday and was not available for
comment.
   The child, whose family has asked that he not be identified, was
found early Thursday by another driver and was taken to a hospital
where he was treated and discharged.
   The boy's parents didn't miss him Wednesday night because they
thought he was staying at a city-run center overnight. Center
officials thought he was at home because he had been absent due to
illness Monday and Tuesday.
   The boy suffers from autism or some other type of disorder that
prevents him from communicating. School officials and the boy's
parents have declined to specify the disorder.
   School officials continued to investigate whether the special
education personnel who work with the boy failed to follow proper
procedures and should be charged with misconduct.
