<FIRST>u s AM-BBO--Angels-Brewers     03-11 0196</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BBO--Angels-Brewers,180</SECOND>
<DATELINE>CHANDLER, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lance Parrish drove in three runs with a
pair of doubles Saturday as the California Angeles defeated the
Milwaukee Brewers 9-5.
   Devon White also provided three runs for the Angeles, two of them
in the fourth inning and another on a grounder to second during a
five-run outburst in the seventh.
   Parrish doubled home a run in the sixth and added two RBIs in the
seventh.
   Johnny Ray singled three times and had two RBIs for California,
whose exhibition record is 5-5.
   Don August started for Milwaukee, 6-4, giving up four hits and
two runs in four innings.
   Leo Perez took the loss, going two innings and allowing four runs
on four hits.
   Angels rookie Jim Abbott pitched three innings in relief. He
retired the first six batters he faced before the Brewers collected
two hits and two runs.
   Brewers team physician Paul Jacobs confirmed that lefthanded
pitcher Juan Nieves has a problem with a rotator cuff that will keep
him idle for about 10 days.
   If the rest period doesn't help the shoulder and surgery is
required, Nieves could be out for four to six weeks. Jacobs said.
</TEXT>
